        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 1:58PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 158 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from over Federal Heights to over Morrison,
or extending from 10 miles northwest of Denver to 14 miles southwest
of Denver, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Denver, western Aurora, Lakewood, southern Thornton, Arvada,
Westminster, southwestern Centennial, southwestern Broomfield,
Highlands Ranch, Commerce City, Littleton, Northglenn, Brighton,
Englewood, Wheat Ridge, Golden, Greenwood Village, Evergreen,
Federal Heights and Roxborough Park.
</description>
